{"actual_usd":0.12401,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":170,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24292,"reply":"\"I wouldn't jump there that fast.\" *I rub a bit of dried clay from my thumb with my forefinger, watching it flake onto the table.* \"In that kind of summary, a man names the heartwood first—Christ died, was buried, was raised, was seen. If Paul says he was buried and then raised, the empty tomb's sitting there under the boards whether he spells it out or not.\"\n\n*I lean back a touch, the bench giving a soft creak.* \"A short telling leaving out one detail isn't the same thing as that detail being invented later. What matters more to me is whether the first witnesses are treating the resurrection like a real thing that happened in the world, not a misty spiritual metaphor—and Paul sure sounds like he is. What's making that omission loom so large for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":64.27191499999999,"run_id":"44b42d2a-d739-43f0-b044-45d66f8f1b59"}
